WEBVTT

00:01.827 --> 00:04.526
ADULT ADAM: The '80s was the peak of the sports comedy,

00:04.569 --> 00:06.615
and my favorite,
Major League.

00:06.658 --> 00:09.705
I loved the classic underdog
story of a team of misfits

00:09.748 --> 00:12.882
who used questionable
methods and voodoo
to become champions.

00:12.925 --> 00:14.710
They actually make
sports tolerable

00:14.753 --> 00:16.712
with their on-field
shenanigans.

00:16.755 --> 00:19.758
And Barry loved the unhinged, badass pitcher, "Wild Thing."

00:19.802 --> 00:23.719
Dude, Wild Thing can't control
his rage or his fastball.

00:23.762 --> 00:25.068
That's just like me.

00:25.112 --> 00:26.765
ADULT ADAM: Yep,
there was nothing better
than rooting

00:26.809 --> 00:28.637
for the ragtag team
with the evil owner.

00:28.680 --> 00:29.942
You want us to lose?

00:29.986 --> 00:33.337
What I want is for us
to finish dead last.

00:33.381 --> 00:35.209
ADULT ADAM:
And then one day,
Major League

00:35.252 --> 00:36.558
became a major reality.

00:36.601 --> 00:38.168
You wanted to see me, Earl?

00:38.212 --> 00:40.475
Ah, there's
my favorite shop teacher.

00:40.518 --> 00:41.693
We should
cut the chitchat.

00:41.737 --> 00:43.652
I have 63 birdhouses
to grade.

00:43.695 --> 00:46.959
See, that is just
the kind of statement
that leads me to believe

00:47.003 --> 00:49.310
you're the perfect man
to help me out.With?

00:49.353 --> 00:51.921
I want to get rid of
the baseball team.Sure.

00:51.964 --> 00:54.315
See, Coach Mellor's departure
has left the team in shambles.

00:54.358 --> 00:55.446
Sure.

00:55.490 --> 00:57.927
They're so bad
that even the school paper

00:57.970 --> 01:00.147
has stopped trying
to spin the losses.

01:00.190 --> 01:02.497
If our team keeps playing
like hot garbage,

01:02.540 --> 01:05.456
I could convince the board
to drop the program

01:05.500 --> 01:08.416
and spend that money
fixing our budgeting issues.Sure.

01:08.459 --> 01:11.158
Which is why you're gonna
be our new baseball coach.

01:11.201 --> 01:13.247
What? I don't know anything
about the game.

01:13.290 --> 01:15.379
A-All I played growing up
were timber sports.

01:15.423 --> 01:16.511
Timber sports?

01:16.554 --> 01:18.121
Log rolling,
speed felling,

01:18.165 --> 01:19.470
speed whittling,
speed sanding.

01:19.514 --> 01:22.473
Yeah, you help me lose and
that absurd radial arm saw

01:22.517 --> 01:25.259
you've been requesting
is all yours.Batter up.

01:25.302 --> 01:27.565
I have taken the liberty
of tracking down

01:27.609 --> 01:29.437
some new recruits
for the team.

01:29.480 --> 01:31.395
They all
happen to be students

01:31.439 --> 01:34.137
who have been dodging
their athletic requirements,

01:34.181 --> 01:36.574
if you catch my drift.
Good luck.

01:36.618 --> 01:39.229
ADULT ADAM: And with that, Mr. Crosby set out to assemble

01:39.273 --> 01:41.275
the worst high-school team
of all time.

01:41.318 --> 01:43.451
Would you look at that?
My shoes are untied.

01:43.494 --> 01:45.801
Better lace these up
before I trip.

01:45.844 --> 01:47.803
That is a wrap on
whatever the hell this is.

01:47.846 --> 01:49.631
Get your hands and feet
to the gym, boys.

01:49.674 --> 01:52.373
All right,
you've died of dysentery.
Time to play sports.

01:52.416 --> 01:53.722
Can I save my...
Go! Get your ass
to the gym.

01:53.765 --> 01:54.940
Go, go, go,
go, go, go.

01:54.984 --> 01:56.768
Come with me, Dave Kim.

01:56.812 --> 01:58.074
Is this about my birdhouse?

01:58.118 --> 01:59.945
I need an extension.

01:59.989 --> 02:02.122
David Sirota, Jessie Wudders,
stop playing
pretend government

02:02.165 --> 02:03.601
and start playing
real baseball.

02:03.645 --> 02:05.516
But I-I only own
penny loafers.

02:05.560 --> 02:06.952
This is gonna be
easier than I thought.

02:06.996 --> 02:08.650
ADULT ADAM: Needless to say,

02:08.693 --> 02:10.826
my brother wasn't thrilled
with our team's new rookies.

02:10.869 --> 02:12.088
I don't get it.

02:12.132 --> 02:14.221
We haven't won a game
all season.

02:14.264 --> 02:16.310
Now they're hamstringing us
with you turds?

02:16.353 --> 02:18.094
Hey, we don't
wanna be here either.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.965
And what are you wearing?

02:20.009 --> 02:22.968
Coach was a uniform short,
so I'm wearing my costume
from Damn Yankees.

02:23.012 --> 02:25.101
Adam, today is
my first pitching start,

02:25.145 --> 02:26.885
and they are
not gonna ruin it.

02:26.929 --> 02:29.671
Relax.
We're just here to satisfy
our sports requirement.

02:29.714 --> 02:31.847
There's no chance Coach
will ever put us in.

02:31.890 --> 02:33.414
Okay, listen up, team.

02:33.457 --> 02:35.459
There's been some changes
to the starting lineup.

02:35.503 --> 02:37.200
Shortstop... Dave Kim.

02:37.244 --> 02:38.810
No!

02:38.854 --> 02:41.465
He's, like, the worst Dave Kim
of all the Dave Kims.

02:41.509 --> 02:42.771
CROSBY: Moving on.

02:42.814 --> 02:44.468
Playing right field,
Adam Goldberg.

02:44.512 --> 02:45.774
What?

02:45.817 --> 02:48.864
He's got a lazy eye
and the body to match.

02:48.907 --> 02:51.649
Normally, I'd object
but I'm desperate here.

02:51.693 --> 02:54.826
Look at it.
These eyes cannot
catch a baseball.

02:54.870 --> 02:57.960
Oh, God. Put back on
the corrective lenses,
man. Please.

02:58.961 --> 03:00.571
♪ Wild thing ♪

03:04.096 --> 03:05.968
ADULT ADAM:
It was January 30,
1980-something,

03:06.011 --> 03:07.970
a landmark day for Gerica.

03:08.013 --> 03:10.059
Happy Kissa-versary.

03:10.102 --> 03:12.104
Here are some tulips
to celebrate the day

03:12.148 --> 03:14.019
these two lips first kissed
those two lips.

03:14.063 --> 03:15.804
Ew. But also aww.

03:15.847 --> 03:17.109
And wait, there's more.

03:17.153 --> 03:19.155
I also booked us a romantic
getaway to the Poconos.

03:19.199 --> 03:20.852
Poconos?

03:20.896 --> 03:23.072
That's our most scenic
and budget-friendly
mountain range.

03:23.115 --> 03:24.726
You know it.
Get packing, lady.

03:24.769 --> 03:26.467
This is amazing.

03:26.510 --> 03:28.599
The two of us, alone.

03:28.643 --> 03:30.732
How did you convince
your dad to say yes?

03:30.775 --> 03:32.908
Oh, it was easy.
Uh, mostly because
I haven't done it yet.

03:32.951 --> 03:34.605
But I have a foolproof plan.

03:34.649 --> 03:35.432
I'm going to lie to him.

03:36.999 --> 03:38.870
Well, this was a fun ride.

03:38.914 --> 03:40.220
I'll just rent us a movie.

03:40.263 --> 03:42.178
Oh, come on. What,
are you implying
I can't lie?

03:42.222 --> 03:43.440
I can lie.
I lie all the time.

03:43.484 --> 03:45.181
You really don't.
And when you do,

03:45.225 --> 03:47.183
you bail immediately
and then overcompensate

03:47.227 --> 03:49.054
by revealing
a deeply personal secret

03:49.098 --> 03:50.534
that nobody wants to know.

03:50.578 --> 03:53.363
Surely you're
thinking of some other
unskilled liar.

03:53.407 --> 03:55.104
Hey, Mom,
Geoff has some thoughts

03:55.147 --> 03:56.758
on your new
Jazzercise ensemble

03:56.801 --> 03:58.194
that he wants
to share with you.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.283
Ah, don't you just love it,
Geoffrey?

04:00.327 --> 04:02.198
The Lycra is form-fitting,

04:02.242 --> 04:03.895
but it still gives me
the freedom

04:03.939 --> 04:05.419
to explore all my moves.

04:05.462 --> 04:08.335
Uh, well, I suppose
I enjoy the bold colors

04:08.378 --> 04:10.554
and the sleeve
length and...
Oh, my God.

04:10.598 --> 04:11.990
Also, one time
at summer camp,

04:12.034 --> 04:14.123
I took a puff of a cigar
and then it made me
really nauseous

04:14.166 --> 04:15.472
and I threw up in a lake.

04:15.516 --> 04:17.387
And there it is.

04:17.431 --> 04:20.564
ADULT ADAM: And so it was
up to my sister to concoct
the perfect lie.

04:20.608 --> 04:24.220
The Eastern Pennsylvania
Scholastic Achievement Awards?

04:24.264 --> 04:26.570
That's fantastic,
but it doesn't surprise me

04:26.614 --> 04:28.442
my Geoffrey is
receiving such an honor.

04:28.485 --> 04:30.226
Well, it's really
an award for you, too.

04:30.270 --> 04:31.401
You raised a smarty.

04:31.445 --> 04:32.794
Take some videos.

04:32.837 --> 04:34.491
Okay, well,
we'll see ya when we see ya.

04:34.535 --> 04:36.885
ADULT ADAM: While Erica
and Geoff lied their way
to a dream weekend,

04:36.928 --> 04:39.191
I was living a true nightmare.

04:39.235 --> 04:40.541
Please don't let
the ball come to me.

04:40.584 --> 04:42.456
Please. Oh, balls.

04:42.499 --> 04:44.936
I-I don't got it!
I don't got it!

04:44.980 --> 04:46.286
I definitely don't got it!

04:47.722 --> 04:49.767
Turns out,
our underdog team

04:49.811 --> 04:52.466
wasn't as bad as the one
inMajor League.

04:52.509 --> 04:53.945
No, we were worse.

04:56.296 --> 04:57.906
I'm as mad at me
as you are.

04:57.949 --> 05:00.909
Boys are looking lousy
out there, Crosby.
Good coaching.

05:02.824 --> 05:04.869
Whoa.
Kremp can actually play.

05:04.913 --> 05:06.784
Yeah, that's on me.

05:06.828 --> 05:08.090
Kid was making
a weird movie
with Goldberg.

05:08.133 --> 05:09.483
I made some assumptions.

05:09.526 --> 05:11.528
Kremp, you're benched
for showboating.

05:11.572 --> 05:12.355
Penny loafer, you're in.

05:13.530 --> 05:15.489
In my defense,
I have cleats,

05:15.532 --> 05:16.707
but you insisted
I wear these.

05:16.751 --> 05:18.274
CROSBY: Uh-huh.
Move it, penny loafer.

05:18.318 --> 05:20.624
Can I just stand
in the grass area?
They're getting all dusty.

05:20.668 --> 05:22.931
Yeah, you do
what you need to do, kid.

05:22.974 --> 05:24.715
ADULT ADAM: And the cherry
on top of our suck sundae,

05:24.759 --> 05:26.543
my brother's pitching.

05:28.023 --> 05:29.546
Just a bit outside.

05:30.765 --> 05:32.506
Ball four.

05:32.549 --> 05:33.855
Ball eight.

05:33.898 --> 05:35.335
Honestly, I've lost count.

05:38.207 --> 05:40.644
ADULT ADAM: I just couldn't
stop wondering why
Crosby and Ball

05:40.688 --> 05:43.778
didn't seem to care that our team was so epically bad.

05:43.821 --> 05:45.562
And then it hit me.

05:48.478 --> 05:50.306
The ball just punched me.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.264
They wanted us to lose,
like inMajor League.

05:52.308 --> 05:55.659
Meanwhile, my sister was
on a major romantic getaway.

05:55.703 --> 05:57.531
You know, I gotta admit,

05:57.574 --> 05:59.054
the whole time
you were lying to my dad,

05:59.097 --> 06:01.883
I had this feeling
that something terrible
was gonna happen.

06:01.926 --> 06:04.451
Stick with me, Schwartz.
I'll never lead you wrong.

06:07.715 --> 06:08.759
Oh, my God!

06:11.675 --> 06:13.329
ADULT ADAM: Yep,
this is 100% true.

06:13.373 --> 06:16.288
My oldest sibling snuck off
on a romantic getaway

06:16.332 --> 06:18.639
and actually did this
to my dad's car.

06:21.293 --> 06:23.078
Oh, God!
What are we gonna do?

06:23.121 --> 06:25.994
Cars don't just fall
off cliffs at scholastic
award shows!

06:26.037 --> 06:27.256
Forget the awards!

06:27.299 --> 06:28.910
My dad's car
just rolled off a cliff!

06:28.953 --> 06:30.651
Oh, my dad's gonna kill me!

06:30.694 --> 06:33.218
Please make sure
some nice lady gets
my eyes! Promise me!

06:33.262 --> 06:34.437
Okay, let's just take
a deep breath

06:34.481 --> 06:36.700
of the fresh mountain air
and think.

06:36.744 --> 06:38.920
I lied my way
into this mess.

06:38.963 --> 06:40.661
I can lie my way
out of it.

06:40.704 --> 06:43.141
And just as
the scholastic gala
was ending,

06:43.185 --> 06:46.449
Geoff and I walked outside
and found a sack
of abandoned puppies.

06:46.493 --> 06:49.104
Naturally, we raced the car
to the animal hospital,

06:49.147 --> 06:51.585
but there was
a drawbridge being raised

06:51.628 --> 06:53.717
and we tried to jump it
for the puppies

06:53.761 --> 06:56.111
because we're good people,
but the car didn't make it.

06:57.721 --> 06:59.375
Luckily, we're fine

06:59.419 --> 07:00.811
and so were
the two dozen puppies

07:00.855 --> 07:02.247
that have now
all found homes.

07:02.291 --> 07:04.467
Drawbridges are death ramps.

07:04.511 --> 07:07.514
My nail girl's brother
tried to jump a drawbridge.

07:07.557 --> 07:10.560
They found
his head and torso
on a fishing trawler.

07:10.604 --> 07:13.607
He's in culinary school now,
but every day is a struggle.

07:13.650 --> 07:15.304
Thank God
the two of you
were not hurt.

07:15.347 --> 07:16.523
It's a lie.

07:16.566 --> 07:18.525
We were in the Poconos
on a secret getaway.

07:18.568 --> 07:20.744
We parked your station
wagon on the hill without
the parking brake,

07:20.788 --> 07:22.529
and also I copied part of
my Bar Mitzvah speech

07:22.572 --> 07:24.487
from a Winston Churchill
biography.

07:24.531 --> 07:26.750
So you lied
right to my face,
Geoffy?

07:26.794 --> 07:29.057
Wait, no. It...
It's not Geoff's fault.

07:29.100 --> 07:31.712
It's all mine,
and I'm so sorry.

07:31.755 --> 07:33.365
ADULT ADAM: And then
my sister braced herself

07:33.409 --> 07:35.193
for a nuclear Murray meltdown.

07:36.978 --> 07:39.720
You sent my car off a cliff!

07:39.763 --> 07:41.504
Wow, he's taking this
really well.

07:41.548 --> 07:43.332
I figured that he would be
screaming his head off.

07:43.375 --> 07:45.290
Off a cliff!
Who does that?

07:45.334 --> 07:48.511
Oh, no.
Your father has reached
a stage beyond anger.

07:48.555 --> 07:51.645
All my family does
is wreck my car!

07:51.688 --> 07:53.255
Third time this year!

07:53.298 --> 07:55.170
Oh, this is not good.

07:55.213 --> 07:56.301
The Poconos.

07:56.345 --> 07:57.564
You could've been killed.

07:57.607 --> 07:59.696
To be honest,
I'm digging this way more

07:59.740 --> 08:01.219
than the screaming
and the "moron" calling.

08:01.263 --> 08:04.571
My insurance is
gonna go through the roof!

08:04.614 --> 08:06.486
Okay, I got to get him inside
and try to calm him down

08:06.529 --> 08:07.791
with warm milk
and Steak-umms.

08:07.835 --> 08:10.359
I don't know if it'll work,
but I'm a desperate woman.

08:10.402 --> 08:14.668
Anyway, I-I'm sorry about
the bending the truth thing.

08:14.711 --> 08:15.712
It probably
won't happen again.

08:15.756 --> 08:17.584
The only reason Geoff
is in this mess

08:17.627 --> 08:19.281
is because of
your terrible influence,

08:19.324 --> 08:21.370
and it stops now.

08:21.413 --> 08:22.937
This relationship is over.

08:22.980 --> 08:25.983
What?
Y-You can't break up
with my girlfriend.

08:26.027 --> 08:27.550
W-Wait, can you? Can he?

08:27.594 --> 08:29.552
I don't know.
I've never been in
this situation before.

08:29.596 --> 08:32.207
Let's go, son.

08:32.250 --> 08:33.948
ADULT ADAM: While Erica's lies had finally caught up to her,

08:33.991 --> 08:37.386
I was catching up the guys
on my major revelation.

08:37.429 --> 08:40.215
Gentlemen, Principal Ball
and Mr. Crosby

08:40.258 --> 08:42.913
are Major Leagueing
this team.What?

08:42.957 --> 08:45.699
Just one glaring problem
with your theory.

08:45.742 --> 08:48.615
If he wanted us to lose,
they'd never let me pitch.

08:48.658 --> 08:51.313
Barry, he let you pitch
because of how bad you are.

08:51.356 --> 08:52.923
Adam. A word?

08:52.967 --> 08:55.709
Just between us,
the last thing I would want

08:55.752 --> 08:57.928
is for me to seem weak
in front of the team,

08:57.972 --> 09:01.279
but what you just said
about my pitching
hurt me to the core.

09:01.323 --> 09:02.629
Uh, bro?

09:02.672 --> 09:04.456
We can hear
everything you're saying.

09:04.500 --> 09:05.588
You're, like,
not that far away.

09:07.285 --> 09:09.244
I'm sorry.

09:09.287 --> 09:10.680
I just thought
it was important
you all know the truth.

09:10.724 --> 09:12.900
But I don't suck.

09:12.943 --> 09:15.076
I'm literally gonna
cry right now.

09:15.119 --> 09:16.991
Guys, it's not so much
a distance thing

09:17.034 --> 09:19.428
as a volume thing, 'cause
we're getting every word.

09:19.471 --> 09:22.300
Damn it!
I'll prove how good
I am right now!

09:22.344 --> 09:23.432
Who's got a ball?

09:23.475 --> 09:24.781
I've got a tangerine.

09:24.825 --> 09:27.523
But it's supposed to be
for emergency dips
in my blood sugar.

09:27.567 --> 09:29.481
This is an emergency.

09:29.525 --> 09:31.614
What are you doing?
I'm gonna throw

09:31.658 --> 09:33.747
this little embarrassing
emergency orange at you

09:33.790 --> 09:36.010
so you can feel
how much I don't suck.

09:39.622 --> 09:41.929
Dude. We're being Major League'd.

09:41.972 --> 09:43.670
What are we gonna do?
I'll tell you what.

09:43.713 --> 09:45.759
We're gonna Major League
'em right back.

09:45.802 --> 09:47.543
'Cause in the end,
it turns out

09:47.587 --> 09:49.850
that ragtag bunch
of losers win it all!

09:49.893 --> 09:51.547
And so will we!

09:51.591 --> 09:55.029
Or we put all our faith
in our amazing pitcher

09:55.072 --> 09:56.683
to take us
to the championship.

09:56.726 --> 09:58.119
Wild Thing.

09:58.162 --> 09:59.381
Look alive,
Shernicke.

10:00.991 --> 10:03.777
Okay, we can just go
with his thing.

10:07.128 --> 10:08.999
ADULT ADAM:
Even though Earl Ball
wanted us to lose,

10:09.043 --> 10:12.089
I'd use my favorite
sports movie to help us win.

10:12.133 --> 10:15.919
Okay, our Major Leaguejourney
from underdog scrubs

10:15.963 --> 10:18.356
to skilled champions
begins with one thing.

10:18.400 --> 10:21.925
Meet Jobu, the idol
that Pedro Cerrano prays to

10:21.969 --> 10:23.710
that helps you hit
the curve ball.

10:23.753 --> 10:27.496
Uh, bro? That doll seems
a little super insensitive.

10:27.539 --> 10:29.454
He's hilarious in the movie,

10:29.498 --> 10:31.848
but presenting it now
just makes me feel
kinda weird.

10:31.892 --> 10:33.241
Y-Yeah, I'd...
I'd put it away.

10:33.284 --> 10:34.808
Okay, we're gonna lose.

10:34.851 --> 10:36.505
Not if we have
a sexy incentive
for us to win.

10:36.548 --> 10:38.072
Aw, yeah,
like in the movie.

10:38.115 --> 10:39.551
Whenever the Indians
would win,

10:39.595 --> 10:42.163
they would remove
a sliver of clothing from
a cardboard cutout

10:42.206 --> 10:44.382
of the team's super hot
yet evil owner.

10:44.426 --> 10:47.995
Which is why
I made a cardboard
cutout of our nemesis,

10:48.038 --> 10:50.040
school principal
and avid swimmer,
Earl Ball.

10:53.957 --> 10:55.916
Relax.
We're only gonna
take a piece off

10:55.959 --> 10:57.091
when we don't win.

10:57.134 --> 10:58.440
This team shall never
lose again.

10:58.483 --> 11:00.268
We can't let it
happen, guys.

11:00.311 --> 11:02.487
For sure! But also, where did
you get that picture?

11:02.531 --> 11:04.359
Finally,
we have to band together

11:04.402 --> 11:05.882
and address
each of our weaknesses.

11:05.926 --> 11:07.362
Like in the movie

11:07.405 --> 11:10.147
when the team had to convince
Wild Thing to wear glasses.

11:10.191 --> 11:13.150
Bro, I-I think someone would
know if they needed glasses.

11:13.194 --> 11:16.197
Not to be this guy,
but we're all painfully aware

11:16.240 --> 11:18.416
that you're super nearsighted
but refuse to acknowledge it.

11:18.460 --> 11:20.114
I can see just fine.

11:20.157 --> 11:22.464
I'll prove it.
I'll read your shirt.
"Spice Inventors."

11:22.507 --> 11:24.118
ALL: No.
"Spork Investors"?

11:24.161 --> 11:25.815
No.
"Shark Incisors"?

