13:40.820 --> 13:43.300
I'm confused,
but ready to act with anger.

13:43.344 --> 13:45.520
Good. 'Cause now we're at
the top of our game,

13:45.563 --> 13:46.913
and nothing can
bring us down.

13:46.956 --> 13:48.610
Well, look who it is.

13:48.653 --> 13:50.264
It's the JTP,

13:50.307 --> 13:52.483
AKA the Jenkintown Posers.

13:52.527 --> 13:54.834
You know that's not
what it stands for, bro!

13:54.877 --> 13:56.705
Balls, balls,
this just got bad fast.

13:56.748 --> 13:58.402
It was the Meadowbrook Mafia,

13:58.446 --> 14:01.362
the JTP's rival posse
from one town over,

14:01.405 --> 14:05.540
and they were led by theater
star and hotshot athlete
Bradley Cooper.

14:05.583 --> 14:08.325
Word on the suburban street is
the baseball schedule changed

14:08.369 --> 14:11.720
and now we get to
destroy you on Friday.

14:11.763 --> 14:13.069
Doesn't matter
who we play,

14:13.113 --> 14:14.854
'cause as long as
I'm pitching,

14:14.897 --> 14:17.465
we're guaranteed the "W."

14:17.508 --> 14:19.293
Can't wait to see you
on the mound, four-eyes.

14:19.336 --> 14:20.772
Shows what you know.

14:20.816 --> 14:22.818
I'm pitching,
not my nerd brother.

14:22.862 --> 14:24.733
No, you're
the four-eyed nerd.

14:24.776 --> 14:26.169
I can't wait
to hit your first pitch

14:26.213 --> 14:28.998
all the way
to the school library.

14:29.042 --> 14:30.565
Where you'll probably find it
the next day,

14:30.608 --> 14:32.697
because you have glasses

14:32.741 --> 14:34.786
and thus an uncool love
of reading.

14:34.830 --> 14:37.311
Well, I'll have you know
Barry never reads.

14:37.354 --> 14:39.008
He's more of a TV guy.

14:39.052 --> 14:41.663
"I have glasses,
and I'm a Dork Lord."

14:44.057 --> 14:47.016
They just called me
a four-eyed nerdling.

14:47.060 --> 14:48.975
That's so hurtful.

14:49.018 --> 14:52.326
Who talks to people like that
just because they wear
corrective lenses?

14:52.369 --> 14:55.068
You? Almost every
single day of my life?

14:55.111 --> 14:57.244
Well, yeah, 'cause you're
a four-eyed nerdling...

14:57.287 --> 15:00.334
Oh, no!

15:00.377 --> 15:01.857
I get it now!

15:01.901 --> 15:05.078
You're just now getting
that being called a nerd
is hurtful?

15:05.121 --> 15:07.341
Yes. Now that
I'm affected,
I care.

15:07.384 --> 15:09.734
Great. 'Cause we actually
have a chance

15:09.778 --> 15:11.432
to stand up
and fight back.

15:11.475 --> 15:12.781
No, guys...

15:12.824 --> 15:14.174
I can't wear these things.

15:14.217 --> 15:16.437
What's the worst
that happens?

15:16.480 --> 15:19.353
Look, there's a reason
I refused to admit
I needed these things.

15:19.396 --> 15:21.572
Yeah, I act all cool,
but I'm not.

15:21.616 --> 15:23.705
And these glasses
will just make it worse.

15:23.748 --> 15:25.750
I'm sorry.
I can't do it.

15:28.623 --> 15:30.277
ADULT ADAM: Turns out
my overconfident brother

15:30.320 --> 15:32.018
was more insecure
than I thought.

15:32.061 --> 15:34.237
And while glasses
made Barry quit the team,

15:34.281 --> 15:36.413
Geoff was determined
to see Erica,

15:36.457 --> 15:38.024
no matter how risky.

15:38.067 --> 15:40.200
Gah! Geoff,
what are you doing?

15:40.243 --> 15:41.810
I'll stop at nothing
to see you!

15:41.853 --> 15:44.552
That's sweet, but you could've
just used the front door.

15:44.595 --> 15:46.380
It's your dad who doesn't
want us together.

15:46.423 --> 15:48.904
Oh, God, I'm so upset
I'm not thinking straight.

15:48.948 --> 15:51.254
Relax. You're forgetting
that I have parents, too.

15:51.298 --> 15:53.865
And once Beverly Goldberg
hears that your dad

15:53.909 --> 15:55.737
called her baby girl
a bad influence,

15:55.780 --> 15:57.391
she'll unleash
such unbridled fury

15:57.434 --> 15:59.088
that your dad will wish
he was in that car.

16:00.263 --> 16:02.265
Yeah, not my place.

16:02.309 --> 16:04.006
Not your place?

16:04.050 --> 16:06.400
Everywhere's your place!
You have no boundaries!

16:06.443 --> 16:09.055
Schmoo, how do I
put this delicately?

16:09.098 --> 16:10.839
We agree with Lou.

16:10.882 --> 16:12.667
You're a horrible influence
on the boy.

16:12.710 --> 16:14.930
What? You're supposed
to be on my side.

16:14.974 --> 16:17.237
Oh, how do I put this
delicately?

16:17.280 --> 16:20.370
Geoff is a college-bound
future doctor.

16:20.414 --> 16:22.720
You're a drop-out liar
who can't even hold a job.

16:22.764 --> 16:24.853
Would you just let her put it
delicately one time?

16:24.896 --> 16:26.333
Look, Erica,

16:26.376 --> 16:28.291
we don't think you're
not good enough for Geoff.

16:28.335 --> 16:29.901
It's just that, right now,

16:29.945 --> 16:32.730
it seems Geoff
is too good for you.

16:32.774 --> 16:35.124
Thank you, Mom.

16:35.168 --> 16:36.604
Wait. That's exactly
the same thing.

16:36.647 --> 16:39.128
You just said it in
a nicer tone.

16:39.172 --> 16:40.260
ADULT ADAM:
For the first time,

16:40.303 --> 16:42.610
my mom said no
to defending her kids

16:42.653 --> 16:44.133
and then felt so bad,
she caved.

16:44.177 --> 16:45.178
Hey.

16:46.831 --> 16:48.442
Wanna talk about it?

16:48.485 --> 16:50.357
Everyone was right.

16:50.400 --> 16:52.489
Geoff deserves someone
better than me.

16:52.533 --> 16:54.883
Schmoo, when I see that boy

16:54.926 --> 16:58.800
and how much he loves you
and how hard he tries,

16:58.843 --> 17:01.411
makes me wonder if maybe
you could be trying
a little harder, too.

17:03.196 --> 17:06.329
I love Geoff so much.

17:06.373 --> 17:08.288
The last thing I want to do
is hold him back.

17:08.331 --> 17:10.812
And, in this case,
maybe that means

17:10.855 --> 17:12.422
I don't get to
be with him,

17:12.466 --> 17:14.511
no matter how much
I want to.

17:20.865 --> 17:22.563
ADULT ADAM: The big game
against Meadowbrook
was starting,

17:22.606 --> 17:23.694
and everyone was there...

17:23.738 --> 17:26.132
Everyone, that is,
except Barry.

17:26.175 --> 17:27.263
CROSBY:
Goldberg, you're up.

17:27.307 --> 17:28.917
Swing or don't swing.

17:28.960 --> 17:30.353
How you strike out
is up to you.

17:30.397 --> 17:32.007
The moment had arrived.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.574
I'd never been a sports hero,

17:33.617 --> 17:35.576
butMajor League taught me
anything was possible.

17:37.099 --> 17:37.969
Just not this time.
Oh, God!

17:38.013 --> 17:39.580
My tender boy body.

17:39.623 --> 17:40.972
Adam?

17:41.016 --> 17:42.713
Barry?
Are you dead, too?

17:42.757 --> 17:43.932
Oh, I'm alive.

17:43.975 --> 17:46.543
And I'm sick of
being a joke.

17:46.587 --> 17:48.241
I'm gonna get revenge
for you,

17:48.284 --> 17:49.894
and every other
four-eyed nerd out there.

17:51.809 --> 17:54.769
Coach, I'm pitching
next inning.

17:54.812 --> 17:56.727
Good thinking.
They're only up a run.

17:56.771 --> 17:58.642
Go get us into a jam.

17:58.686 --> 18:01.080
ADULT ADAM: Barry didn't
just come back to our team
to defend my honor,

18:01.123 --> 18:04.561
he returned to show the world he was finally done with hiding who he really was.

18:05.910 --> 18:08.043
♪ Wild thing

18:08.087 --> 18:10.176
♪ You make my heart sing

18:11.873 --> 18:13.179
ADULT ADAM: Yep, it's true.

18:13.222 --> 18:16.182
After years of calling me
a four-eyed Dork Lord,

18:16.225 --> 18:19.098
Barry Norman Goldberg
now had glasses.

18:19.141 --> 18:22.318
What is this song?
Where is it even coming from?

18:22.362 --> 18:24.581
Oh, yes.
Just like his hero,

18:24.625 --> 18:26.366
Rick "Wild Thing" Vaughn
inMajor League,

18:26.409 --> 18:28.324
Barry could finally
see clearly,

18:28.368 --> 18:30.979
and he'd use it to win
once and for all.

18:31.022 --> 18:32.154
