18:36.854 --> 18:39.205
That day, Barry didn't use
his new glasses

18:39.248 --> 18:40.858
to strike out
the other team.

18:40.902 --> 18:42.730
Instead,
he struck 'em down,

18:42.773 --> 18:45.385
and it felt glorious.

18:48.605 --> 18:50.085
You're out of here!

18:50.129 --> 18:53.044
ADULT ADAM: In that moment,
I had a new sports hero...

18:53.088 --> 18:54.698
Barry "Wild Thing" Goldberg.

18:55.699 --> 18:57.571
Hey, get up.
What?

18:57.614 --> 19:00.051
You heard me.
Get up. Get dressed.

19:00.095 --> 19:01.618
Maybe run a comb
through your hair.

19:01.662 --> 19:02.793
Why? Where are we going?

19:02.837 --> 19:04.621
To get Geoff back.

19:04.665 --> 19:06.014
What about Lou?

19:06.057 --> 19:08.886
If he thinks he's gonna
keep my baby from
the man she loves,

19:08.930 --> 19:12.412
then he's gonna find out
what a bad influence I can be.

19:14.805 --> 19:17.199
ADULT ADAM:
Yep, no one messes
with Beverly Goldberg.

19:17.243 --> 19:18.853
Sure, it took her a while
to get onboard,

19:18.896 --> 19:22.204
but now Geoff's dad
was about to face off
with our Wild Thing.

19:22.248 --> 19:23.379
Evening, Lou.

19:23.423 --> 19:26.643
Thank you for coming
to this ambush.

19:26.687 --> 19:29.472
How dare you say my daughter
isn't good enough for your...

19:29.516 --> 19:30.691
Mom, wait.

19:30.734 --> 19:32.214
I know I begged you
to fix this,

19:32.258 --> 19:34.042
but this is something
I have to do on my own.

19:34.085 --> 19:35.130
But I'm all revved up.

19:35.174 --> 19:37.001
Please, rev down.
I got this.

19:37.045 --> 19:40.048
Look, I know I get
Geoff into trouble

19:40.091 --> 19:41.484
and force him
out of his comfort zone

19:41.528 --> 19:44.444
and have him throw parties
in your living room.

19:44.487 --> 19:46.620
But there is not
a slide show in the world

19:46.663 --> 19:48.796
that will make you see just
how much I love your son.

19:48.839 --> 19:51.277
Even though
I'm selfish and moody

19:51.320 --> 19:53.061
and have so much
growing up to do,

19:53.104 --> 19:55.194
you still love me.

19:55.237 --> 19:58.893
So, yeah, I'm not nearly
good enough
for a guy like you.

19:58.936 --> 20:01.635
But you make me wanna do
whatever it takes
to prove I can be.

20:03.550 --> 20:05.943
Maybe they do bring out
the best in each other.

20:05.987 --> 20:07.771
No maybe, Lou.

20:07.815 --> 20:09.991
They just do.

20:10.034 --> 20:12.602
ADULT ADAM: Sometimes
we've got to fight
for what we love,

20:12.646 --> 20:15.475
but what good is a fight
without a little backup?

20:15.518 --> 20:17.303
Just a bit outside.

20:17.346 --> 20:19.261
That's the thing
about family.

20:19.305 --> 20:20.654
You're a team...

20:20.697 --> 20:22.830
A team that never stops
believing in each other.

20:22.873 --> 20:24.527
And when that happens,

20:24.571 --> 20:26.964
it makes everything
a little more groovy.

20:27.008 --> 20:28.531
♪ Wild thing ♪

20:32.970 --> 20:34.929
ADULT ADAM: How come
when I wear glasses,
you call me a nerd,

20:34.972 --> 20:36.496
but when you wear glasses
you look awesome?

20:36.539 --> 20:38.149
That's not very fair.

20:38.193 --> 20:39.368
ADULT BARRY:
I like the glasses.

20:42.241 --> 20:44.765
Okay.
Move, dumbass.
We can't see.

20:44.808 --> 20:46.723
I know.
I was once like you.

20:46.767 --> 20:50.161
But thanks to major advances
in contact-lens technology,

20:50.205 --> 20:53.339
I now have the vision of
an eagle holding a telescope.

20:53.382 --> 20:54.992
Now that I have
better-than-perfect vision,

20:55.036 --> 20:57.560
a whole new world of careers
has opened up for me.

20:57.604 --> 20:58.692
Behold.

20:58.735 --> 21:01.347
I can now be
a fighter pilot,
umpire,

21:01.390 --> 21:03.566
professional Where's Waldofinder,

21:03.610 --> 21:06.439
avid reader,
guy who writes
things on rice,

21:06.482 --> 21:10.617
long-distance peeping tom,
and Olympic athlete.

21:10.660 --> 21:12.358
It's a tad late to start
training for the Olympics.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.751
Not with these
laser-focused baby browns.

21:14.795 --> 21:17.014
Oh, God, my contact lens
popped out.

21:17.058 --> 21:19.539
Help.
Help me.

21:19.582 --> 21:21.976
Mark my words,
if Barry somehow makes it in,

21:22.019 --> 21:23.151
it will be the most
memorable thing

21:23.194 --> 21:24.500
to ever happen
at the Olympics.
